29/06/2010
JERUSALEM, Israel -- A panel tasked with investigating last month's deadly raid against a Turkish-led flotilla carrying aid to Gaza began work in Jerusalem on Monday (June 28th). The five-member panel will question Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, Defence Minister Ehud Barak and military Chief of Staff Gaby Ashkenazi about the raid, which left nine Turkish activists dead. The commission is composed of local officials and two foreign observers. (AP, Hurriyet, AFP - 28/06/10)
